41 files

[7] DESIGN -------------------------------------------------------------------

The 'srcmod' consists of two key parts:

    * Application files 
    * Source module files

1. Application Files

The application files make up collection of tools to manage a given source
module. Such tools currently include:

    * ./authors 
    * ./build 
    * ./changelog 
    * ./files 
    * ./install 
    * ./package 
    * ./readme 
    * ./setup 
    * ./tasks 
    * ./uninstall 

2. Source module files

The source module files consist of everything that belongs to a given source
module. In the current release, these include:

    2.1 Descriptors 

        * ./API 
        * ./AUTHORS 
        * ./BACKGROUND 
        * ./BUILD 
        * ./CHANGELOG 
        * ./DEFECTS 
        * ./DEPENDENCIES 
        * ./DESCRIPTION 
        * ./DESIGN
        * ./EXAMPLES
        * ./FEATURES 
        * ./INSTALL 
        * ./LICENSE
        * ./README 
        * ./REQUIREMENTS 
        * ./SOURCES 
        * ./TASKS 
        * ./TEST 
        * ./VERSION 

    2.2 Templates

        * ./template.bash.executable 
        * ./template.bash.variable 
        * ./template.bash.function 
        * ./template.bash.test 
        * ./template.bash.configuration 
        * ./template.gitignore 

    2.3 Variables

        * ./variable.[name]
        * ./variable.[name]
        * etc. 

    2.4 Functions

        * ./function.[name]
        * ./function.[name]
        * etc. 

    2.5 Tests

        * ./test.[name]
        * ./test.[name]
        * etc. 

    2.6 Configurations

        * ./configuration.[name]
        * ./configuration.[name]
        * etc. 

[8] SOURCES ------------------------------------------------------------------

Source code can be obtained on GitHub (https://github.com/kz9676/srcmod).

Presently, I have one active branch:

    * origin/development  - is the main branch where the source code of HEAD
                            always reflects a state with the latest delivered
                            development changes for the next release

